original_title: Brooklyn: St. Edwards Street - Leo Place
text:
St. Edwards Street, east side, north from Leo Place to Tillary Street, showing Public School No. 67 and several tenements and an old church, which were later demolished to make way for the erection of an addition to the elementary school. The tenements are numbers 77, 67, and 65. The church edifice is St. Augustines Protestant Episcopal Church and is number 69-75.

October 31, 1927

P.L. Sperr

(2)

The new addition to Public School No. 67.

April 27, 1940

P.L. Sperr

original_title: Brooklyn: St. Edwards Street - Leo Place
text:
69-75 St. Edwards Street, east side, at Leo Place, showing the Ebenezer Wesleyan Methodist Episcopal Church, formerly St. Augustine's Protestant Episcopal Church. The church was later razed, together with the adjoining buildings, to make way for the erection of an addition to Public School No. 67.

July 1, 1934
Views 1,2

P. L. Sperr
